{"article_id":"CCKFxnp8fHX4oNc8","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Tropical Storm Harvey continued to hit southeastern Texas on Sunday with `` catastrophic flooding '' in Houston ,","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"forcing residents to flee to their roofs and higher ground","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"as officials respond to thousands of 911 calls for rescues in the `` unprecedented '' event .","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"The National Hurricane Center 's 7 p.m. CDT advisory shows the center of Harvey 120 miles southwest of Houston .","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"Forecasters said","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"`` some slight re-strengthening is possible","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"after the center moves off the coast on Monday night and Tuesday . ''","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"Rainfall from Harvey could reach up to 50 inches in some spots ,","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"making it the highest ever","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"recorded in the state ,","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"the National Weather Service announced .","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"`` This event is unprecedented","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"and all impacts are unknown and beyond anything experienced .","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"Follow orders from officials","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"to ensure safety , ''","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"the National Weather Service wrote on Twitter .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"The storm has so far affected about a quarter of the Texas population , or 6.8 million people in 18 counties .","depth":6},{"id":17,"text":"Several hundred people arrived at the George R. Brown Convention Center in downtown Houston ,","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"which officials are using as a shelter","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"as floodwaters have inundated much of the city .","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"The center was also used as a shelter for Hurricane Katrina refugees in 2005 .","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"The Red Cross is prepared to manage 1,000 people at the convention center .","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"Authorities throughout Houston and the surrounding Harris County area are opening shelters","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"as thousands continue to evacuate their homes","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"due to severe flooding .","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"Texas Gov . Greg Abbott said during a news conference Sunday afternoon","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"that Texas has now activated 3,000 National and State Guard members","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"to combat the severe flooding and damage","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"resulting from the storm .","depth":12},{"id":29,"text":"Abbott added","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"that 500 vehicles and 14 aircraft have been put into service .","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"Harris County Judge Ed Emmett asked","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"that anyone","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"who has a boat or a high water vehicle","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"to help with rescue efforts in the Houston area .","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"Those","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"sent to Houston","depth":13},{"id":37,"text":"to help from outside the city","depth":13},{"id":38,"text":"are unable to enter due to flooded roadways .","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"`` We desperately need boats and high water vehicles , ''","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"Emmett said .","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"`` We ca n't wait for assets to come from outside . ''","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"Between 1,500 and 2,000 high-water rescues have been conducted","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"since Harvey began wreaking havoc in the area ,","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"the Harris County Sheriff 's Department wrote .","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"Houston Police Chief Art Acevedo wrote on Twitter","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"that Houston Police have `` completed 90 flood rescue missions","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"resulting in over 1,100 community members being brought to safety . ''","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"Houston Mayor Sylvester Turner said in a news conference Sunday","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"more than 2,000 calls to 911 for rescues have been made ,","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"assuring","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"priority has been given to life-threatening calls .","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"Turner also defended his previous decision","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"not to ask residents to evacuate","depth":13},{"id":54,"text":"before the heavy rain swamped roads .","depth":13},{"id":55,"text":"`` If you think","depth":15},{"id":56,"text":"the situation right now is bad","depth":15},{"id":57,"text":"and you give an order","depth":15},{"id":58,"text":"to evacuate ,","depth":15},{"id":59,"text":"you are creating a nightmare , ''","depth":13},{"id":60,"text":"Turner said .","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"The director of the Federal Emergency Management Agency , Brock Long , said","depth":12},{"id":62,"text":"the government is expected to conduct a `` mass care mission ''","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"and predicted","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"that the aftermath of the storm would require FEMA 's involvement for years .","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"More than 1,200 FEMA employees have been deployed","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"to assist with Harvey response .","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"`` This disaster 's going to be a landmark event , ''","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"Long said .","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"Acevedo said","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"the city 's 911 system has been `` overwhelmed ''","depth":12},{"id":71,"text":"since Harvey struck .","depth":12},{"id":72,"text":"`` Do not call 911","depth":14},{"id":73,"text":"unless it is a life or death situation ...","depth":14},{"id":74,"text":"[ we 're telling people ] not to panic , ''","depth":13},{"id":75,"text":"Acevedo said ,","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"adding","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"that `` we have n't seen the worst of it yet . ''","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"Houston residents ,","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"attempting to escape the water","depth":13},{"id":80,"text":"quickly rising in their homes ,","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"were spotted on top of gates outside their homes and on kayaks .","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"Acevedo urged residents not to go to their attics","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"and instead seek refuge on their roofs .","depth":12},{"id":84,"text":"`` Reports of people getting into attic","depth":14},{"id":85,"text":"to escape floodwater","depth":14},{"id":86,"text":"- do not do so","depth":14},{"id":87,"text":"unless you have an ax or means","depth":15},{"id":88,"text":"to break through onto your roof , ''","depth":15},{"id":89,"text":"Acevedo wrote on Twitter .","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"Rising rainwater also forced Ben Taub Hospital , Harris County 's public hospital , to be evacuated","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"and patients to be dispersed to nearby hospitals","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"because flooding problems in the basement are disrupting power service .","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"The water was waist-deep at the Level 1 trauma center .","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"`` We 're going to get the sickest patients out first , ''","depth":13},{"id":95,"text":"Bryan McLeon , a spokesman for the Harris Health System said .","depth":13},{"id":96,"text":"`` We have 16 or 17 people on ventilators . ''","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"McLeod said","depth":13},{"id":98,"text":"the staff is making sure","depth":14},{"id":99,"text":"everything is being done properly ,","depth":15},{"id":100,"text":"including the transfer of medical records and charts .","depth":15},{"id":101,"text":"He added :","depth":13},{"id":102,"text":"`` Our staff has been performing heroically . ''","depth":13},{"id":103,"text":"Harris County sheriff 's spokesman Jason Spencer said","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"flooding throughout the county","depth":13},{"id":105,"text":"that includes Houston and the region","depth":13},{"id":106,"text":"is so widespread","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"that it 's `` difficult to pinpoint the worst area . ''","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"Acevedo said","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"rainwater threatens to bring more flooding into the city in the coming days","depth":12},{"id":110,"text":"as it trickles down from other parts of the state .","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"`` [ I ] can not emphasize enough how much flooding there is on roadways .","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"You are endangering yourself and our first responders","depth":14},{"id":113,"text":"by being out .","depth":14},{"id":114,"text":"Stay put , ''","depth":13},{"id":115,"text":"Acevedo wrote on Twitter earlier .","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"Meanwhile , Harris County Sheriff Ed Gonzalez and Turner continued urging residents on Twitter to `` shelter in place ''","depth":6},{"id":117,"text":"and stay off rain-swollen roadways .","depth":6},{"id":118,"text":"Gonzalez actively used Twitter overnight Sunday","depth":8},{"id":119,"text":"to field assistance for those trapped inside water-soaked homes , attics and vehicles .","depth":8},{"id":120,"text":"Those","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"appealing for assistance or being steered to help via Gonzalez 's Twitter feed included a person","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"suffering `` cardiac-arrest , ''","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"and a woman","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"who posted :","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"`` I have 2 children with me","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"and the water is swallowing us up .","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"Please send help . ''","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"Gonzalez at one point appealed for calm and patience ,","depth":7},{"id":129,"text":"saying","depth":8},{"id":130,"text":"officials were `` trying to make it to everyone","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"as best we can . ''","depth":9},{"id":132,"text":"Aransas County Sheriff Bill Mills said","depth":7},{"id":133,"text":"at least 35 of the emergency vehicles in his fleet have broken windows and windshields","depth":8},{"id":134,"text":"and are out of service .","depth":8},{"id":135,"text":"The smashed windows on the vehicles allowed rainwater to get inside ,","depth":8},{"id":136,"text":"which shorted out the electronics in the vehicles","depth":9},{"id":137,"text":"and set off their sirens and lights mid-storm .","depth":9},{"id":138,"text":"Mills said","depth":8},{"id":139,"text":"some vehicles had six inches of water in them .","depth":8},{"id":140,"text":"A sinkhole opened on a two-lane Texas highway , Farm-to-Market 762 , about 25 miles southwest of Houston .","depth":7},{"id":141,"text":"Rosenberg Police tweeted a picture of the sinkhole ,","depth":8},{"id":142,"text":"which could be seen filling with water .","depth":8},{"id":143,"text":"The department asked people to avoid the area .","depth":6},{"id":144,"text":"Flights from William P. Hobby and George Bush Intercontinental airports were halted","depth":9},{"id":145,"text":"due to standing water on the runways ,","depth":9},{"id":146,"text":"according to Fox 26 .","depth":8},{"id":147,"text":"Thousands of flights were canceled","depth":8},{"id":148,"text":"and travelers were left stranded in the area .","depth":8},{"id":149,"text":"The U.S. Army Corps of Engineers plans to begin releasing water Monday morning from the Barker and Addicks Reservoirs","depth":9},{"id":150,"text":"to prevent uncontrollable flooding of downtown Houston and the Houston Ship Channel .","depth":9},{"id":151,"text":"The dams were built during the 1940s in response to a 1935 flood","depth":9},{"id":152,"text":"that inundated much of downtown Houston .","depth":9},{"id":153,"text":"Col. Lars Zetterstrom said","depth":8},{"id":154,"text":"the water","depth":11},{"id":155,"text":"contained in the dams","depth":11},{"id":156,"text":"is `` unparalleled in the dams ' history , ''","depth":10},{"id":157,"text":"with waters rising about 4 inches per hour .","depth":9},{"id":158,"text":"Harvey made landfall as a Category 4 hurricane late Friday night ,","depth":8},{"id":159,"text":"but downgraded to a tropical storm by Saturday .","depth":8},{"id":160,"text":"The hurricane center said in its 4 a.m. Sunday update","depth":8},{"id":161,"text":"that the tropical storm has maximum sustained winds of 45 mph","depth":9},{"id":162,"text":"and remains stationary about 45 miles northwest of Victoria , Texas .","depth":9},{"id":163,"text":"At least one person died due to the flooding ,","depth":11},{"id":164,"text":"Houston Fire Department 's Sheldra Brigham said .","depth":11},{"id":165,"text":"Paramedics found the individual in a vehicle just before 10 p.m.","depth":11},{"id":166,"text":"A doctor , a passerby","depth":14},{"id":167,"text":"who stopped","depth":15},{"id":168,"text":"to help ,","depth":15},{"id":169,"text":"was already at the scene","depth":13},{"id":170,"text":"and pronounced the person dead .","depth":12},{"id":171,"text":"A second person was confirmed dead in a house fire","depth":10},{"id":172,"text":"as the hurricane came ashore Friday night .","depth":10},{"id":173,"text":"Aransas County Judge C.H . `` Burt '' Mills Jr. told the Austin American-Statesman","depth":9},{"id":174,"text":"that 12 to 14 other people were injured .","depth":9},{"id":175,"text":"Harris County Flood Control District Meteorologist Jeff Lindner said","depth":11},{"id":176,"text":"all of the county 's 22 watersheds have spilled over their banks","depth":12},{"id":177,"text":"and are experiencing record flooding .","depth":12},{"id":178,"text":"Watersheds are creeks and bayous","depth":11},{"id":179,"text":"that take water away from the Houstin area","depth":12},{"id":180,"text":"and eventually drain into Galveston Bay .","depth":12},{"id":181,"text":"It may take until Sunday night , well into Monday or possibly Tuesday `` to get the water out of these areas","depth":11},{"id":182,"text":"that have been impacted so hard , ''","depth":11},{"id":183,"text":"Lindner said .","depth":10},{"id":184,"text":"A video ,","depth":10},{"id":185,"text":"taken from aboveground","depth":11},{"id":186,"text":"and posted to Twitter by the Coast Guard Heartland ,","depth":11},{"id":187,"text":"shows an unidentified area","depth":10},{"id":188,"text":"majorly submerged in water as part of the aftermath of Harvey .","depth":10},{"id":189,"text":"The White House confirmed Sunday","depth":7},{"id":190,"text":"that Trump will travel to Texas on Tuesday .","depth":7},{"id":191,"text":"Press Secretary Sarah Sanders said","depth":7},{"id":192,"text":"the White House is working to coordinate the logistics of his trip with state and local officials .","depth":7},{"id":193,"text":"The president had previously tweeted","depth":8},{"id":194,"text":"that he would go to Texas","depth":9},{"id":195,"text":"`` as soon as that trip can be made","depth":10},{"id":196,"text":"without causing disruption .","depth":10},{"id":197,"text":"The focus must be life and safety , ''","depth":8},{"id":198,"text":"Trump tweeted .","depth":8},{"id":199,"text":"The president said on Saturday","depth":9},{"id":200,"text":"he was `` closely monitoring '' the storm from Camp David .","depth":9},{"id":201,"text":"On Sunday evening , Trump took to Twitter","depth":9},{"id":202,"text":"to add","depth":10},{"id":203,"text":"that with the `` HISTORIC rainfall in Houston , and all over Texas , '' that the `` Spirit of the people in incredible . ''","depth":10},{"id":204,"text":"Abbott said","depth":9},{"id":205,"text":"Trump 's response to the storm was `` extremely professional , very helpful ''","depth":10},{"id":206,"text":"and offered any resources","depth":11},{"id":207,"text":"the governor needed .","depth":11},{"id":208,"text":"He added","depth":9},{"id":209,"text":"it 's still unclear what amount of money will be needed for storm damage repairs ,","depth":10},{"id":210,"text":"but estimated to be `` billions of dollars . ''","depth":10},{"id":211,"text":"Abbott on Sunday said","depth":7},{"id":212,"text":"the number of counties","depth":9},{"id":213,"text":"declared federal disaster areas","depth":9},{"id":214,"text":"has increased from six to 18 , a number","depth":9},{"id":215,"text":"which has been approved by Trump .","depth":9},{"id":216,"text":"There have already been 50 counties","depth":9},{"id":217,"text":"declared state disaster zones -","depth":9},{"id":218,"text":"30 earlier in the week and 20 on Saturday .","depth":8},{"id":219,"text":"Nearly seven million people live in the 18 counties","depth":9},{"id":220,"text":"now covered by the disaster declaration","depth":10},{"id":221,"text":"Trump approved ,","depth":10},{"id":222,"text":"including Houston","depth":9},{"id":223,"text":"- the nation 's fourth-largest city .","depth":9},{"id":224,"text":"During the news conference Sunday , Abbott thanked a number of states for their help","depth":8},{"id":225,"text":"providing resources in Texas ,","depth":8},{"id":226,"text":"including Nebraska , Tennessee , Utah , California , Missouri , Ohio , Arizona and New York .","depth":7},{"id":227,"text":"The Coast Guard ,","depth":8},{"id":228,"text":"which received more than 300 requests for help ,","depth":8},{"id":229,"text":"deployed five helicopters","depth":8},{"id":230,"text":"and asked for additional aircraft from New Orleans .","depth":8},{"id":231,"text":"Harvey arrived as the fiercest hurricane","depth":4},{"id":232,"text":"to hit the U.S. in 13 years","depth":4},{"id":233,"text":"and the strongest","depth":4},{"id":234,"text":"to strike Texas since 1961 's Hurricane Carla , the most powerful Texas hurricane on record .","depth":4},{"id":235,"text":"For those","depth":4},{"id":236,"text":"who want to help those affected by Harvey ,","depth":4},{"id":237,"text":"please visit www.RedCross.org .","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":475,"left":468,"right":474,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":468,"left":369,"right":467,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":369,"left":253,"right":368,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":253,"left":240,"right":252,"re